snippet.textDisplay: The soul of the stotram got lost in the mayhem of this fusion. I am in full support of artistic freedom, but one really needs to listen to it being chanted in a temple to realise how intense it sounds and how entranced you would be. If that was done, perhaps the composers would have approached this track very differently.

snippet.textDisplay:
Um, as other comments state, it is not a "traditional Tamil prayer". The stotram is in Sanskrit supposedly composed by Adi Sankaracharya (though some sources say it was composed by Ramakrishna Kavi). It is fine to experiment with mixing different song/styles, but the facts need to be correct. 

I'm not a fan of the guitar riffs here...I think that is a bit of a mismatch in this song.
